e after three miles  We were reporting every    minutes  I was transmitting During the competition  Begalowski and Pekala represented UIC  They were one of only    teams accepted to participate in a podium session  where they presented the rocket they are working on with mechanical and industrial engineering assistant professor Patrick Lynch in his laboratory at UIC laboratory Other UIC team members who attended the competition included mechanical and industrial engineering students Matthew Valenzeno  Rachel Cruz  and Marcin Maksimowicz  and computer science students Thomas Hein and Corey Habel The AIAA chapter at UIC is a student run organization dedicated to the study of aerospace and propulsion engineering  Apart from high powered rockets  the students also design and build remote controlled aircraft and quad copters AIAA chapter at UIC  n nContact n nUIC News contributor n nuictoday uic edu n n n nCategories n nTop Student News  n Contact  nUIC News contributor n nuictoday uic edu n UIC News contributor uictoday uic edu Categories  nTop Student News  Top Student News Topics American Institute of Aeronautics and Astronautics  engineering  mechanical and industrial engineering  rocket American Institute of Aeronautics and Astronautics engineering mechanical and industrial engineering rocket  n nUIC Logo n n n n UIC Logo  n         t  Today n       t t   Contact uictoday uic edu Social Media Accounts For the Media Experts Guide Advertise in UIC News Submit Announcements Submit an Event Subscribe to UIC Today UIC edu links UIC edu Academic Calendar Athletics Campus Directory Disability Resources Emergency Information Event Calendar Job Openings Library Maps UI Health Veterans Affairs Privacy Statement Campuses University of Illinois System Urbana Champaign Springfield 